html.body: RB-E2F molecular interactions map RB-E2F is detailed and manually curated comprehensive map of molecular interactions of the cell cycle in the context of the retinoblastoma protein (RB/RB1). Deregulations and/or mutations in cell cycle players in general and in the RB pathway in particular are observed in most human cancers. The RB-E2F map contains 78 proteins, 176 genes, 99 protein complexes,165 chemical reactions and based on 350 publications. The map has modular organization and composed of 17 interconnected functional modules.
